<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[685,1172,601,1233]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,814,601,622]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[737,869,627,648]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marskeae">
<emphasis box="[737,869,627,648]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">C. marskeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with a pronotal blue patch immediately anterior to scutellum (Woodley and Touroult 2012: fig. 2). It can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[685,815,707,728]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marskeae">
<emphasis box="[685,815,707,728]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">C. marskeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its narrow aedeagus, which is at least 3.4 times as long as wide (Woodley and Touroult 2012: figs. 5, 6). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Descarpentries" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guadeloupensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Chrysobothris guadeloupensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also the only species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaeffer" authorityYear="1905" box="[685,826,813,834]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[685,701,813,834]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[723,826,813,834]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speies-group known from the 
<collectingCountry box="[685,804,840,861]" name="Guadeloupe" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Guadeloupe</collectingCountry>
archipelago. For a full description, see Woodley and Touroult (2012).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[685,1172,601,1233]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,789,893,914]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Length.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[803,938,892,914]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.35" metricValueMax="6.2" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="5.35" valueMax="6.2" valueMin="4.5">4.5– 6.2 mm</quantity>
(from Woodley and Touroult 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="84" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[685,1172,601,1233]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,840,946,967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is reported from the islands of Grande Terre, Basse Terre, and La Désirade in 
<collectingCountry box="[870,1000,999,1020]" name="Guadeloupe" pageId="3" pageNumber="84">Guadeloupe</collectingCountry>
(Woodley and Touroult 2012).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
